<p>Choosing the right words can be challenging, but sincerity and genuine concern always outweigh eloquence.  Avoid overly formal language; instead, opt for simple, heartfelt expressions that reflect your genuine emotions.  Remember to focus on offering comfort and support rather than trying to fix the situation.  Your presence and empathy, expressed through a carefully considered message, can make a profound difference in a grieving friend's journey through their sorrow.</p>
    

